## Interview Notes

### What is an IDS?

> An Intrusion Detection System is a passive security technology that monitors network traffic or host activity for malicious behavior and generates alerts when suspicious activity is detected. Unlike an IPS, an IDS provides visibility into potential attacks but does not block traffic.

---

### IDS vs IPS

| IDS | IPS |
|------|-----|
| Detects threats | Detects and blocks threats |
| Passive | Active (Inline) |
| Generates alerts | Generates alerts and prevents attacks |
| Does not modify traffic | Can block or drop malicious traffic |

